               <msContents>
                  <summary>Homily [in Honor] of [the
                            Archangel] Michael (Dərəsanä Mika'el) <p>Fols. 10v, 11rv, 12v, passim: The owner's names Haylä Maryam and
                                Wälätä Maryam appear at the beginning and ending of every text.
                                </p>
                     <p> Fols. 9v, 11rv, 12v, passim: The scribe's name Wäldä Eləyas
                                appears at the beginning and ending of every text. </p>
                     <p> Fols.
                                105rv: Pen trial.</p>
                     <p> No miniatures.</p>
                     <p> Late 18th century
                                with 20th-century additions.</p>
                     <p>In a later hand.</p>
                     <p>In later
                                hand, a poem and a note in Amharic in green pen, largely illegible
                                dated "30/12/52" EC [August 1959
                                AD].</p>
                     
                     <p>References: See references for
                                manuscript no. 21.</p>
                  </summary>
